cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on distributed deep learning and proposes a new scheduling framework for efficient job scheduling on high-performance GPU clusters. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper deals with deep learning training jobs and proposes algorithms to optimize the job completion time. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new scheduling framework and algorithms to optimize the performance of a system consisting of multiple distributed training jobs. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper considers communication contention between nodes in a cluster and proposes algorithms to efficiently schedule communication tasks. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also relevant as the paper aims to maximize the overall performance of the cluster when training multiple jobs simultaneously.
